==English==
===Etymology===
From '''all''' + '''one''', Old English '''[[al one]], [[all allone]]''', Anglo-Saxon '''[[an one]]''', alone.  See [[all]], [[one]], [[lone]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈlon/

===Adjective===
# By one's self; apart from, or exclusive of, others; single; solo; solitary;&mdash;applied to a person or thing.
#* ''I can't ask for help because I am alone.''  That is, &ldquo;I am alone&rdquo; means nobody else is near.
# Of or by itself; by themselves; without any thing more or any one else; without a sharer; only.
#* ''Man shall not live by bread alone.'' &mdash;Luke iv. 4.  Here, &ldquo;bread alone&rdquo; means bread and nothing else.

Note: The adjective alone commonly follows its noun.


